<section>
<h1>After Builders Cleaning vs Deep Cleaning</h1>

<p>
After renovation work many property owners assume a standard deep clean is
sufficient. In reality, post-construction environments create a different
type of contamination that requires specialised cleaning processes.
</p>

<p>
Understanding the difference between after builders cleaning and deep
cleaning helps determine the correct service following refurbishment or
heavy property use.
</p>

</section>

<section>

<h2>What Is After Builders Cleaning?</h2>

<p>
After builders cleaning is a specialist cleaning process designed to remove
construction residue following renovation or installation work.
</p>

<ul>
<li>Fine plaster and cement dust removal</li>
<li>Adhesive, silicone and installation residue cleaning</li>
<li>Detailed fixture and frame extraction</li>
<li>High-level dust removal</li>
<li>Multiple vacuum passes for fine particulate</li>
</ul>

<p>
This process typically occurs after kitchen installations, plastering,
property extensions or full refurbishments.
</p>

</section>

<section>

<h2>What Is Deep Cleaning?</h2>

<p>
Deep cleaning focuses on removing accumulated domestic dirt, grease and
general build-up within a property.
</p>

<ul>
<li>Kitchen degreasing</li>
<li>Bathroom descaling</li>
<li>Appliance cleaning</li>
<li>Carpet vacuuming</li>
<li>General surface sanitation</li>
</ul>

<p>
Deep cleaning is usually required after extended occupancy, pre-sale
preparation or periodic maintenance cleaning.
</p>

</section>

<section>

<h2>Key Differences</h2>

<ul>
<li><strong>Source of contamination</strong> — construction dust vs domestic build-up</li>
<li><strong>Cleaning equipment</strong> — HEPA extraction vs standard cleaning tools</li>
<li><strong>Dust management</strong> — staged extraction vs single-pass cleaning</li>
<li><strong>Typical trigger</strong> — renovation completion vs property maintenance</li>
</ul>

</section>

<section>

<h2>When After Builders Cleaning Is Required</h2>

<ul>
<li>Plastering work has been completed</li>
<li>Kitchen or bathroom installations finished</li>
<li>Floor sanding projects</li>
<li>Extension or refurbishment work</li>
<li>New build property handovers</li>
</ul>

<p>
In these environments construction dust and installation residue require a
specialist cleaning sequence.
</p>

</section>

<section>

<h2>When Deep Cleaning Is More Suitable</h2>

<ul>
<li>General property refresh</li>
<li>Pre-sale preparation</li>
<li>Heavy domestic build-up</li>
<li>Seasonal maintenance cleaning</li>
</ul>

</section>

